      "lang": "en",
      "term": "A pattern of substance use that leads to damage to an individual's physical or mental health or results in behavior leading to physical or psychological harm to others. The pattern of substance use is observed for a minimum of 12 months for occasional use or at least one month for continuous use (daily or nearly daily). Health damage results from intoxication behaviors, direct or secondary toxic effects on body organs and system or harmful method of substance intake. Harm to others encompasses any physical or mental harm directly attributable to the user's intoxicated behavior.",
